      <method name="alloc_wrapped"
              c:identifier="gst_d3d11_allocator_alloc_wrapped"
              version="1.22"
              introspectable="0">
        <doc xml:space="preserve"
             filename="gst-libs\gst\d3d11\gstd3d11memory.cpp"
             line="1854">Allocates memory object with @texture. The refcount of @texture
will be increased by one.

Caller should set valid CPU acessible memory value to @size
(which is typically calculated by using staging texture and Map/Unmap)
or zero is allowed. In that case, allocator will create a temporary staging
texture to get the size and the temporary staging texture will be released.

Caller must not be confused that @size is CPU accessible size, not raw
texture size.</doc>
        <source-position filename="gst-libs\gst\d3d11\gstd3d11memory.h"
                         line="308"/>
        <return-value transfer-ownership="full" nullable="1">
          <doc xml:space="preserve"
               filename="gst-libs\gst\d3d11\gstd3d11memory.cpp"
               line="1874">a newly allocated #GstD3D11Memory with given @texture
if successful, or %NULL if @texture is not a valid handle or configuration
is not supported.</doc>
          <type name="Gst.Memory" c:type="GstMemory*"/>
        </return-value>
        <parameters>
          <instance-parameter name="allocator"
                              transfer-ownership="none"
                              nullable="1"
                              allow-none="1">
            <doc xml:space="preserve"
                 filename="gst-libs\gst\d3d11\gstd3d11memory.cpp"
